result.execSummary:
The defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 2 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 DAYS served FOR A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 07-31-2015 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Adjournment of the currently scheduled plea and sentencing requested.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 1, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defense counsel requests a plea/sentencing date.  Court orders case adjourned to Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  
Defendant to have no contact with: James S; Kasi V; Milw Academy of Chinese Language School.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  
Defendant Cedric Darnell Eichelberger in custody.  
William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  
Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  
DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
